Package: iptables-mod-cluster
Version: 1.8.10-r1
Depends: libc, libxtables12, kmod-ipt-cluster
Source: feeds/base/network/utils/iptables
SourceName: iptables
License: GPL-2.0
Section: net
SourceDateEpoch: 1729551123
URL: https://netfilter.org/
CPE-ID: cpe:/a:netfilter:iptables
Architecture: aarch64_cortex-a53
Installed-Size: 71680
Filename: iptables-mod-cluster_1.8.10-r1_aarch64_cortex-a53.ipk
Size: 3472
SHA256sum: f202da52b5b6b664f7f53bdf5f39436a675ebb3452429377f962e9b0f661322b
Description:  iptables extensions for matching cluster.
 
 Netfilter (IPv4/IPv6) module for matching cluster
 This option allows you to build work-load-sharing clusters of
 network servers/stateful firewalls without having a dedicated
 load-balancing router/server/switch. Basically, this match returns
 true when the packet must be handled by this cluster node. Thus,
 all nodes see all packets and this match decides which node handles
 what packets. The work-load sharing algorithm is based on source
 address hashing.
 
 This module is usable for ipv4 and ipv6.
 
 If you select it, it enables kmod-ipt-cluster.
 
 see `iptables -m cluster --help` for more information.

